The receipt (Evidence 3) shows a purchase of the glass light stand on September 4, the day before the murder. However, Redd White's testimony (Testimony 3) states that he saw the glass light stand already at Fey & Co. Law Offices when he entered to place the wiretap, which could have been earlier than the purchase date on the receipt.

This means White's testimony about seeing the glass light stand is contradicted by the receipt proving the stand was bought only the day before the murder.

